<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At Least 26 Injured in Tornado in Florida </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 2 (Xinhua) -- At least 26 people were
injured in a tornado that skipped across the coast beach in Florida
early today.
</P>
<P>
Many roofs and second floors on houses were torn off as the
tornado lashed over the New Smyrna Beach. A 64-unit condominium
complex was devastated, and about 100 residents of DiamondHead
Point took refuge in their clubhouse.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 200 people have been forced out of their damaged homes
and have relocated to shelters or other homes.
</P>
<P>
A total of 26 people went to Bert Fish Medical Center for
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
