<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Calls for More Cultural Cooperation with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's Crown Price Hassan Ibn
Talal said today that Jordan and China should have more cultural
cooperation in the future through influential and
institutionalized channels.
</P>
<P>
Hassan made the statement when he met Chinese Cultural Minister
Liu Zhongde who arrived here Friday on a three-day official
visit.
</P>
<P>
Both Arab and Chinese cultures had long history and contributed
greatly to the global culture and it was necessary for the two
cultures to increase cooperation, said Hassan during his meeting
with the Chinese guest.
</P>
<P>
A seminar on Arab culture would be held in China next year
and it would give a more comprehensive and accurate image of
the Arab culture to the participants, said the crown prince.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting, Liu told Hassan that the cultural exchange had
been going on smoothly since China and Jordan countries
established diplomatic ties in 1977.
</P>
<P>
China signed a cultural exchange accord with Jordan in 1979
and all the projects under the accord had been realized or was
being realized, Liu informed Hassan, adding that China paid great
attention to its friendship and the cultural exchange with the
kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Liu also met Jordanian Minister of Culture and Youth Qassem
Abu Ein today and both sides discussed means to enhance bilateral
cultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhongde is concluding his visit to Jordan today and is
going to Cairo for a visit to Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
