energy unit at Beloyar nuclear power station, but also in a
project involving a South-Urals station.
</P>
<P>
"Fast reactors are the future of the Japanese energy sector,"
he said. However, Japan had not succeeded in creating such
reactors.
</P>
<P>
"They have problems involving safety aspects, while the safety
of the fast reactors existing in Russia has been proven," the
energy official said.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that getting access to the Japanese internal
market of nuclear fuel is of critical importance for Russia.
</P>
