on October 15 with the help of troops from Angola. He was
imaugurated as President on October 25.
</P>
<P>
Lissouba who became the central African country's first
democratically-elected President in 1992, has fled to Burkina
Faso.
</P>
<P>
Reports say Lissouba is going to visit Washington from
November 3 through 7 to seek support for the restoration of
democracy and free elections, a spokesman for Lissouba said on
Sunday. 
