economy and urban construction are senior managers and chairmen of
27 big-name corporations such as Citibank, General Motors and
Nortel Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
"Learning from experience of big cities overseas, Shanghai must
map out a sustainable development plan at the dawn of a new
century," Mayor Xu Kuangdi said at the ninth International
Entrepreneurs' Counseling Meeting for Shanghai's Mayor which
closed today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting with the theme "Shanghai: Facing the 21st Century,"
discussed how global economic development will affect Shanghai and
the future of the city's pillar industries such as automotives,
telecommunications and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
In 1989, the annual meeting won the approval of the State
Council, China's highest governing body.
</P>
<P>
Xu said next year's meeting will focus on preventing financial
risks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
