<HEADLINE> IAAF Golden Four Series Ended, Source Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Golden Four athletics series
in Oslo, Zurich, Brussels and Berlin has ended, a source close to
the organisers said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The source said the meeting promoters had agreed unanimously to
end the series to avoid clashing with a planned Super League to be
launched by the International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF).
</P>
<P>
The lucrative Golden Four series, which shared 20 one-kilo gold
bars between the athletes who won their event in all four
meetings, was launched in 1993. The four meetings are part of the
IAAF grand prix circuit.
</P>
<P>
An IAAF spokesman confirmed the plan for a Super League. He
said it was unclear when it would start but added it should be
launched in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
