<HEADLINE> India Seeks Cheaper Export Routes to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- India is seeking cheaper
export routes to Russia to double trade between the two countries,
official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The present trade volume between India and Russia stood at 2
billion US dollars. The figure could surpass 5 billion by the turn
of the century through exploration of new cheaper routes.
</P>
<P>
Cheaper routes of exports like the sea route from Mumbai
(Bombay) and Bandar Abbas in Iran and further by rail or roadways
into central Asian countries are being explored.  
</P>
