<HEADLINE> d p s 1343 China-Three Gorges-Passenger Flow Surging Passenger Flow to Three Gorges Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- The upcoming
blocking of the Yangtze River has resulted in a soaring passenger
flow to Yichang, where the Three Gorges Project is located.
</P>
<P>
The number of passengers handled by the city's train station
has climbed about 30 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
"It seemed that the Spring Festival, which usually sees a
biggest passenger flow every year, had come ahead of date,"
said an official at the train station.
</P>
<P>
The city's new airport, which opened to traffic last year, has
also seen unprecedented passenger arrivals, as many as 5000 a
week.
</P>
<P>
Road traffic volume is mounting, with hundreds of buses
shuttling between Yichang and Wuhan, the capital of central Hubei
province.
</P>
<P>
Local telecommunications are also enjoying a brisk business
with increasing inquiries for phone numbers of the China Yangtze
Three Gorges Project Development Corporation, the Gezhouba
Share-holding Group Corporation, and hotels in the city.
</P>
<P>
To meet the growing demand for passenger transportation and
telecommunication business, the city has increased the services
for train and air transportation, installed more
program-controlled phone lines and put a satellite ground station
into operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
