<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Goalkeeper Scores with a Direct Goal-kick </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Goalkeeper Inigo Arteaga of
Racing Ferrol on Sunday became the first Spanish professional to
score directly from a goal-kick in a third division match against
Moralo.
</P>
<P>
Arteaga scored in the 70th minute to put his side in a 2-0
lead. His strong goal-kick flew 100 meters down the area then
bounced straight past the horrified Moralo goalie Jose Peralta.
</P>
<P>
FIFA changed the laws of the game on July 1 that goals straight
from goal-kicks should be counted.
</P>
<P>
Arteaga's feat seal the name of his Racing Ferrol team in
Spainsh record. The Spain's third division team have had little to
shout about in their 80-year history apart from one Spanish Cup
final appearance back in 1935.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0057 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's GDP Up 6.4 Percent for 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Gross Domestic
Product (GDP) grew by 6.4 percent in real terms in the second
quarter of 1997 over a year earlier, further up from the 6.1
percent increase in the first quarter, official statistics
released today showed.
</P>
<P>
Among the major GDP components, private consumption expenditure
rose strongly by 8.7 percent in real terms in the second quarter
as compared with the same quarter last year. This was the fastest
growth rate recorded since the first quarter of 1994.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, government consumption expenditure had a 5.8 percent
increase in real terms.
</P>
<P>
On investment spending, gross domestic fixed capital formation
recorded a large year-on-year increase of 16.2 percent in real
terms in the quarter.
</P>
<P>
In the quarter, Hong Kong's total exports of goods increased by
6.2 percent in real terms, while imports of goods recorded a 6.9
percent growth in real terms.
</P>
<P>
A Government Secretariat spokesman noted that the growth
momentum in the economy continued to be strong, with the GDP
growth rate for the second quarter of this year representing a
further rise from the continuously accelerating trend since the
beginning of last year.
</P>
<P>
He said domestic demand was robust, reflecting a very positive
sentiment, and this bolstered overall growth even when the
performance on the external sector front was relative moderate.
</P>
<P>
He also said that overall inflation in the economy remained
stable, even as economic activity intensified further. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Female Workers in Chinese City Enjoy Maternity Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Female workers in this northeast
China city now receive financial aid from a special social
insurance fund.
</P>
<P>
More than 900,000 female employees, or 95 percent of the city's
total female workers, have been insured over the past two
years.
</P>
<P>
Pregnant women receive at least 1,000 yuan each from the
Maternity Insurance Fund.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the Dalian city government upgraded its social welfare
system by adopting a regulation which requires local enterprises
to pay 0.8 percent of the workers' monthly salaries to the fund.
</P>
<P>
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
