<HEADLINE> PLA Delegation Left for Australia, New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, November 3 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Chinese
People's Libration Amy (PLA) left here today for a good-will visit
to Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by PLA Guangzhou Military Area Commander,
Lieutenant General Tao Bojun, is paying the visit at the
invitation of the Defense Forces of Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the delegation will meet with senior military
leaders of the two countries, exchange views with them on
Sino-Australia, Sino-New Zealand military relations and the
regional security issue of common concern, and visit troops
and military installations in the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
