<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Urged to Implement Agreements With PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Egypt today urged Israel to
implement the signed agreements in its talks with the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA), the Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Ambassador in the United States Ahmed Maher said that
to achieve success in the new round of talks and progress in the
stalled Mideast peace process hinge on the attitude of Israel in
Washington talks, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The PNA President Yasser Arafat's deputy Mahmoud Abbas and
Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy are expected to open their
second round of high-level talks in Washington today after
seven-month standoff.
</P>
<P>
Maher referred to the importance of an Israeli commitment to
the Oslo agreements, completion of redeployment of Israeli troops
in the West Bank and a halt to settlement activities.
</P>
<P>
"Israel should seek effecting a headway to prove good
intentions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he called upon the U.S. to take actions to prove its
seriousness in this connection.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said recently that
Israel will hand over no more land to the PNA and proposed to move
straight to final status talks that will tackle the most thorny
issues like the future of settlements and Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians demand Israel to implement the long-delayed
redeployment of Israeli troops in the rural areas of the West Bank
and stop settlement construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
