<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Scholars Encouraged to Serve Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Wu Jieping, president of the
Western Returned Scholars Association (WRSA), today encouraged
overseas Chinese students to make a contribution to China's
development and its reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Wu asked the WRSA, China's largest non-governmental
organization of returned overseas students, to also provide good
service to returned scholars.
</P>
<P>
Wu, also vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, made his remarks at a meeting of the
WRSA, which was founded in 1913.
</P>
<P>
The organization should serve as a bridge, he said, meaning
that it should not only inform overseas scholars about current
domestic policies but also convey their opinions and needs
to concerned departments to pave the way for them to return and
better serve China.  
</P>
