<HEADLINE> Shanghai Cooperates With VISA to Enlarge ATM Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- China's largest industrial
city and financial hub will cooperate with VISA International to
enlarge the local electronic currency network by increasing the
use of credit cards and intelligent cards (IC), also known as
debit cards.
</P>
<P>
The credit card company will make VISA/INTERLINK cards for use
at member banks in Shanghai through the local ATM/POS network,
according to a letter of intent signed today with the Shanghai
Computer Application and Industry Development Office.
</P>
<P>
VISA also plans to promote the application of IC cards in
Shanghai by providing technical standards and expertise.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai hopes to expand its electronic currency network for
financial and business sectors and to meet international standards
as soon as possible, Shanghai Vice-Mayor Jiang Yiren said at the
signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is trying out the national Golden Card project for
establishing a nationwide electronic currency network.
</P>
<P>
The city set up the first automatic teller machine network in
1995 which was connected with the VISA/PLUS network in
June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
