<HEADLINE> s d s 1006 China-Three Gorges Site Dam Site Warmed up for Blocking of Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Three
Gorges Project site is already immersed in a festive atmosphere
with the final blocking of the Yangtze River drawing near.
</P>
<P>
A reviewing stand has already been erected at the hillside not
far from the northern bank of the Yangtze River, with the
decoration work under way. A gathering site is also to be
constructed at the northern bank where the damming ceremony is to
be held.
</P>
<P>
The damming site is already closed off, and special permit is
needed to access the damming site.
</P>
<P>
To celebrate the grand event, the Three Gorges Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China will also issue 19,970
sets of memorial cards. Each set includes five cards, carrying a
denomination value of 60 yuan each.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition also opened at the dam site today displaying the
initial success achieved in the resettlement for the gigantic Three
Gorges Project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
