<HEADLINE> Coup Leader's Family Evicted From Military House </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Another coup plotter's family
was evicted from an army home here at the weekend, Daily Mail
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Captain Jack Chiti's wife told the local newspaper that an
army truck with eight army officers came to their home in Roma
Township Friday afternoon while she went to police headquarters
to take some food to her husband.
</P>
<P>
She said there was no notice from the army about the eviction
and it caught them unawares.
</P>
<P>
"I returned home in the evening, only to find that my home was
empty. We do not have a permanent home so we just squat with our
relatives," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said the security men have however not harassed her as she
tried to see her husband who she said is being held at police
headquarters although she was not allowed to see him.
</P>
<P>
On the coup attempt, she said the family received the news
with shock when it was discovered that her husband was part of
the group involved in the foiled coup.
</P>
<P>
She explained that the days prior to the "dark" Tuesday, her
husband had been on night duties for seven days.
</P>
<P>
She said Chiti who is a teacher at Arakan Barracks had never
behaved in a peculiar manner because he was of sober character
and very cool person.
</P>
<P>
She said there was a possibility that he could have been
forced into the plot because he had never discussed it with her.
</P>
<P>
"You can imagine what difficulty I am going through as a wife
to one of the men who are alleged to be behind the attempted
coup. Look at the impact it has had on the children. I tell you
this is just like a funeral, may be even worse," she complained.
</P>
<P>
Coup leader Captain Stephen Lungu Alias' family were also
evicted from their Buffalo village home here.
</P>
<P>
Last Tuesday morning, a military coup was staged in the
capital Lusaka by some army soldiers in an attempt to topple the
elected government led by Presidnet Frederick Chiluba.
</P>
<P>
The coup was quickly foiled by government forces and most of
the coupists including coup leaders Captain Steven Lungu Alias,
Captain Solo and Captain Jack Chiti have been arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
