<HEADLINE> Sino-Belgian Economic Ties Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi, meeting here today with Van
Den Brande, Belgian Minister President of the Government of
Flanders, said that China and Belgium are economically
complementary and there is great potential for economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Two-thirds of the 250 Belgian enterprises that have
joint-ventures in China are from Flanders, Wu said, expressing her
appreciation for the efforts of Flanders in enhancing Sino-Belgian
economic links.
</P>
<P>
She went on to say that the Chinese government has again
lowered the tariff rate and has promised to reduce the rate to the
average of developing countries in the year 2000. China will also
adopt more favorable policies for imports of high-tech equipment
and advanced technologies.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the hope that Belgian enterprises will increase
investment in and technology transfers to China, to bring
bilateral economic cooperation to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Brande said that the business community in Flanders is
interested in doing business with China and washes to launch more
joint ventures in China. 
</P>
