<HEADLINE> Chinese, Mongolian Defense Ministers On Military Co-operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Defense Minister Chi
Haotian met today with his Mongolian counterpart Dambyn Dorligjav
today and reached an agreement on cooperation between the defense
ministries of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of China's Central Military Commission
and a state councillor, said dramatic changes have taken place in
the world, and peace and development have become the common goal
of all nations.
</P>
<P>
China appreciates Mongolia's policy of friendly cooperation
with all countries, Chi said, adding that friendly cooperation
between the two close neighbors is beneficial to the maintenance
of peace and tranquility along their borders.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have conducted fruitful cooperation in such
sectors as politics, economy, national defense, science and
technology, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed satisfaction over the progress in bilateral
relations and between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to develop a long-term neighborly relationship
with Mongolia in the 21st century, he said, based on the
principles of peaceful coexistence by carrying out cooperation on
the basis of equality and mutual benefit to promote the
development of both countries, and to safeguard the peace and
stability of the region.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that China will, as always, respect Mongolia's
independence, national sovereignty and territorial integrity, as
well as its status as a nuclear-free zone.
</P>
<P>
Dorligjav said that his visit is aimed at further expanding
military cooperation and strengthening military trust between both
sides.
</P>
<P>
With the steady growth in bilateral relations, co-operation
between the two armed forces has been increasing, he said,
expressing the belief that his visit will promote the relationship
between the two countries and armed forces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
