<HEADLINE> New Investment Upsurge Emerges in South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIHAI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- A new round of investment is
taking place in the coastal city of Beihai in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The city signed 30 contracts with 500 million U.S. dollars of
investment with companies from 13 countries and regions, which
attended the 3rd International Pearl Festival here on October 29-30.
</P>
<P>
Investment is mainly for tourism, transportation and
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The Tropicana of the United States has invested 20 million
U.S. dollars in a large fruit juice-processing factory and a
British company has put 26 million U.S. dollars in the terminal
building at the Beihai airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
