<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors Going To China's Three Gorges Construction Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, November 3 (Xinhua) -- For the past month, the damming
of China's Yangtze River has become the focus of many people, and
as the November 8 date draws near, rooms in most hotels in
Yichang, the closest city to the Three Gorges construction site,
are sold out.
</P>
<P>
People have come to Yichang, which is 40 km from Sandouping,
the dam site, by air, water, and land. Tanziling, the highest spot
on the northern bank of the river, and areas around it, have
become a park where tourists can get a bird's-eye view of the
whole operation.
</P>
<P>
There have even been direct charter flights from Hong Kong to
Yichang as part of a "one million overseas compatriots tour the
Three Gorges" program. And, "one-day tour to construction site of
Three Gorges Project" programs are everywhere. A hundred domestic
and overseas media organizations have sent teams to cover the
event, according to the Three Gorges Project Press Center.
</P>
<P>
Needless to say, many eateries are overjoyed by the new
arrivals, who have also helped the city's entertainment business.
</P>
<P>
The streets of Yichang are decorated with banners welcoming
visitors and the city government has urged service departments to
improve their service to create a good image, and there are
activities to promote economic and trade relations with the
outside world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
