<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Cultural Relics Protection Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has increased the number of protected cultural relics sites, with
an additional 125 sites now under provincial protection.
</P>
<P>
The relics include six stone statues, 11 ruins, 16 ancient
tombs and 92 structures.
</P>
<P>
The province's long history has yielded an abundance of cultural
relics, including the world famous Hemudu Ruins, one of the
earlist birthplaces of the ancient Chinese civilization.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's expanded cultural relics protection efforts over the
past few years include the establishment of 2,000-odd protection
units, including the 323 ones under provincial protection. Related
units now serve as the bases for patriotic education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
