<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Mortality Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The mortality rate in Macao
dropped from 5.2 percent in 1976 to 3.3 percent in 1996, official
figures show.
</P>
<P>
A report released by the Macao Public Health Department said
the general health conditions in Macao have improved remarkably
during the 1976-96 period.
</P>
<P>
The death rate of infants also dropped from 12.6 per thousand
in 1985 to 4.7 per thousand in 1996. That was much lower than most
neighboring regions, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the life expectancy of local residents reached 79
years in 1995, with men at 77.5 and women 81.2. The report said
the figure was much higher than in the Philippines, China's
inland, Thailand, the Republic of Korea, Singapore and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The leading killer diseases in Macao include cardio- and
cerebro- vascular diseases, cancer, respiratory diseases,
injuries, poisoning and other infections.
</P>
<P>
The top killer, cardio- and cerebro-vascular diseases, were
connected with heredity, mal-metabolism and the unhealthy life
style which includes an intake of excessive calories, fat and
alcohol, high pressure, sitting too long and poisoning from
cigarette smoking, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The import of tobacco, the report said, surged from 707 tons in
1985 to 2,921 tons in 1994. Smoking causes cardiovascular diseases
and illness of the respiratory systems.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
