<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese White Dolphin Nature Reserve Set Up in Southeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The city of Xiamen in east China's
Fujian province has recently established an offshore nature reserve for the
Chinese white dolphin.
</P>
<P>
The 5,500-hectare sea reserve is expected to protect the
dolphins. High-speed motorboats that are used for entertainment
and water-skiing have been banned in the area.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese white dolphin is under top State-level protection
because it is on the verge of extinction. They can be found at
Xiamen and the mouth of the Pearl River to the south of here.
</P>
<P>
The number of Chinese white dolphins has declined sharply
because of landfill in the sea, marine pollution, and illegal
fishing by electric devices and explosives.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen also has a local law that protects the dolphin.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
