<HEADLINE> Chinese State Councillor Meets with Lao Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Luo Gan, State Councillor and
Secretary-General of the State Council, met with a
delegation from the Lao Ministry of Interior led by Minister
Asang Laoley here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Zhongnanhai, headquarters of the
central government, Luo said that as good neighbors, the two
countries have smoothly developed friendly cooperation in
the political, economic and other fields through various channels.
</P>
<P>
He noted that a series of agreement signed between relevant
departments of the two countries have greatly pushed forward
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government encourages more Chinese
enterprises to invest in Laos.
</P>
<P>
Laoley expressed satisfaction with the sound cooperation
between the public security departments of the two countries. He
noted that he has held talks with Chinese Minister of Public
Security Tao Siju during his visit.
</P>
<P>
The Lao Ministry of Interior and the Chinese Ministry of Public
Security signed an agreement on coordinating their efforts to
crack down upon international drug trafficking and strengthen law
enforcement along the common borders of the two countries.
</P>
