<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore In Air Exercise with Thailand, US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 3 (Xinhua) -- About 280 personnel from the
Republic of Singapore Air Force (RSAF) are participating in an
annual trilateral air exercise with the Royal Thai Air Force
(RTAF), the U.S. Air Force (USAF), and the U.S. Marine Corps
(USMC), the Defense Ministry announced today.
</P>
<P>
Code-named COPE TIGER, the exercise was launched at the Paya
Lebar Air Base here this morning by senior officers from the air
forces of the three countries involved, the Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In the first phase of the exercise, a five-day Command Post
Exercise will be conducted from today to Friday at the Paya Lebar
Air Base. participants will familiarize themselves in a combined
operating environment through mission planning exercises and
mission commanders' training.
</P>
<P>
In Phase Two, a Flying Training Exercise will be conducted next
February in Korat, Thailand. A total of about 70 aircraft will be
participating in Phase Two, the Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It said the RTAF will deploy their F-16s and F-5s; the USAF and
USMC, their F-16s, F/A-18s and E-3 AWACS; and the RSAF, their
F-16s, F-5s and surface-to-air missile systems.
</P>
<P>
"EX COPE TIGER serves as a platform for professional
interactions and exchanges among participants. It also helps to
foster closer relations and enhance mutual understanding and
goodwill among the three countries," the Ministry said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
