<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese in U.S. Hail President Jiang's Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, November 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 Chinese
scientists, businessmen and visiting scholars in southern
California today hailed the visit to the United States by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
At a luncheon hosted in honor of Jiang, who is winding up his
9-day state visit to the United States, representatives of the
overseas Chinese said that Jiang's visit is a great event in both
China-U.S. relations and in the cause of peace and development in
the world.
</P>
<P>
The "historic and fruitful" summit between Jiang and
U.S. President Bill Clinton has brought the China-U.S. relations
to a new level and laid a firm foundation for the development of
the relations in the next century, said Adam Deng, president of
the South China Association in USA.
</P>
<P>
Establishing a long-term stable and cooperative relationship
between China and the United States is a common wish of all the
Chinese communities in the United States, Deng said, adding that
such a relationship is in the interests of the Chinese in the
United States and conducive to world peace, stability and
development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking amid warm applauses, Jiang expressed thanks to the
Chinese communities in southern California for their positive
contributions to China's construction and the strengthening of the
ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that China-U.S. relations will return to normal after
his visit.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Taiwan, Jiang said it is the common wish of all
the Chinese people, including overseas Chinese, to realize China's
reunification. 
</P>
</TEXT>
