<HEADLINE> Israeli Defense Minister Involved in Mashaal Plot, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai was fully aware of the assassination plot
against the Hamas leader Khaled Mashaal in Jordan, the Jerusalem
Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli intelligence source was quoted by the newspaper as
saying that Mordechai sat in on a detailed briefing given to Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu by Mossad chief Danny Yatom and the
agents who were to carry out the attack.
</P>
<P>
The meeting took place in late August during which the timing
and location of the assassination were settle in the presence of
Netanyahu and Mordechai, the source said.
</P>
<P>
On September 25, Israeli agents assailed Mashaal in Amman.
Failing to killing him, the two agents were arrested by Jordanian
police and the plot was exposed to the public.
</P>
<P>
The botched attack has triggered an uproar in Arab countries
and various political groups or factions in Israel. Israel set up
a committee to investigate the affair to see who were
responsible. While Netanyahu admitted his responsibility,
Mordechai denied his involvement.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai has been regarded as an "honest and righteous" leader
and a rising political star in Israel. But involvement in the
affairs could hurt his image and even political future, observers
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
