<HEADLINE> World Acupuncture Conference Closes in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Academic Conference of the
World Federation of the Acupuncture-Moxibustion Society (WFAS)
closed here today.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference, which attracted over 1,200 experts
from 36 countries and regions, was cosponsored by the WFAS and
the World Health Organization. Conferees presented 863 papers,
including six papers listed as outstanding ones by the Conference
Academic Committee.
</P>
<P>
Conferees suggested the establishment of unified clinical
standards for acupuncture and moxibustion so as to improve
scientific studies on acupuncture theories and promote the
traditional therapy worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The conference provided a positive influence on the development
of acupuncture and moxibustion in the new era, according to Hu
Ximing, chairman of the Chinese Acupuncture and Moxibustion
Society.
</P>
<P>
The WFAS presented honorary certificates to 35 Chinese and
foreign experts for their contribution to the progress of
acupuncture and moxibustion studies worldwide.
</P>
<P>
The next WFAS academic conference will be held in Sidney,
Australia, in the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
