<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Passes Law to Protect Children of Divorce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian Majlis
(parliament) has passed a law to protect children of divorce
and separation of married couples.
</P>
<P>
The law, which was passed Sunday in an open session chaired by
Majlis Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri, made some amendment to
concerned civil laws about children of divorce.
</P>
<P>
The law empowered relevant judicial officials to intervene in
cases where "improper care for the children of divorce or moral
decadence of the guardians jeopardizes the physical or moral
well beings of the children."
</P>
<P>
In the open session, the Majlis also allowed a three month
period for validity of court rulings approving divorce cases and
obliged the divorce registration office to inform the ruling
within the said period, otherwise the decision would be void.
</P>
</TEXT>
