<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Benefits from Foreign Know-How </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Foreign expertise has become an
important factor for the rapid economic development of
Heilongjiang province, northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Since the early 1980s, more than 10,000 foreign experts have
worked in the province, which has also sent 5,000 of its own
people abroad to study.
</P>
<P>
As a major grain producer of China, the province focuses on
importing agricultural technology, which has been used on 8 million
hectares of farmland, bringing more than 8 billion yuan (close to one
billion US dollars) in economic returns.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, some 70 percent of the province's added grain output
was resulted from the imported agricultural technology.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to foreign expertise, the province's industrial
enterprises have increased pre-tax profit by 550 million yuan and
earned some 100 million US dollars in foreign exchange from
exports.
</P>
<P>
Foreign experts have also helped the development of local
education, culture, and public health. 
</P>
</TEXT>
