<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Canal Now Safe for Navigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- The water
diversion canal at the construction site of the gigantic Three
Gorges Dam in China has been doing well since October 6, when it
was opened.
</P>
<P>
According to the Navigation Headqurters at the Three Gorges of
the Yangtze River, 6,000 ships and boats had passed the
3,726-meter canal by last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The canal, on the southern bank of the Yangtze, will be the
only navigable channel for ships and boats after the course of the
rive is closed on November 8 for the construction of the Three
Gorges Dam.
</P>
<P>
The canal will be used along with a temporary ship lock for the
next six years, a headquarters official said.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters is now busy drafting an emergency plan for
smooth navigation of ships on the canal when the Yangtze River
damming takes place on November 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
