<HEADLINE> China Oil Company Witnesses Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The China National Star
Petroleum Corp (CNSPC), the country's third largest oil company,
has forged cooperative ties with oil companies and research
organizations in over 60 countries.
</P>
<P>
CNSPC President Zhu Jiazhen said the corporation is currently
engaged in a number of international oil prospecting and drilling
projects in the Gulf of Mexico, the North Sea, the Sea of Japan,
Russia and Cote d'Ivoire.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that the Sino-Japanese Geological Engineering
Corp (SJGE), a joint venture between the CNSPC and a Japanese
firm, has been operational, and petroleum equipment manufactured
by the SJGE is being exported to the United States, Canada, South
America and Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
The CNSPC has also joined Australian companies in exploration
and marketing of coal-bed methane gas in Shanxi and Shaanxi
provinces. Other projects include a joint appraisal of Hedong
coal-bed methane reserves and a technical cooperation project on
the development of the Yakela oil and gas field with US firms, and
a joint project with Japanese companies to appraise oil reserves in
the basins of the Songhuajiang River and the Liaohe River in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that the CNSPC is striving to achieve an annual oil
and gas production of ten million tons by 2010. 
</P>
