855 projects. Said contracts will be carried out at a cost of 5.6
billion US dollars, including foreign funds of 3.5 billion US
dollars, said Mu Huaishan, director of the Tianjin Municipal
Economic Commission.
</P>
<P>
Some 202 of 318 medium- to large-sized state-owned enterprises
in Tianjin, or 64 percent of the total, have completed
readjustment or technological transformation projects.
</P>
<P>
Various prestigious transnational companies, including Samsong
and the LG Group from the Republic of Korea, and US-based Otis
Elevator have either funded or entered into cooperative ventures
with industrial firms in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to form as many as 10 enterprise groups with
annual output values of over 10 billion yuan each, according to
Mu. 
