<HEADLINE> Development-Oriented Relocation Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- Relocation
programs will mean better lives for approximately 90,000 farmers
who have been displaced from the Three Gorges area, at China's
largest water conservation project.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorge Reservoir will submerge 632 sq km of land in 22
counties and cities in central Hubei province and southwestern
Chongqing municipality, in a relatively impoverished region.
</P>
<P>
To help improve the lives of these displaced people, who may
ultimately number 1.2 million, the central government is adopting
development-oriented programs instead of cash compensation.
</P>
<P>
In the course of implementing the development-oriented
programs, the efforts are focused on setting up grain, fruit and
forest bases on uncultivated land, developing aquaculture in the
reservoir, and improving infrastructure and running rural
enterprises and tertiary industry with state funds and aid from
other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years alone, the state appropriated a total
of 8.58 billion yuan (some one billion US dollars) for the
resettlement purpose. 
</P>
</TEXT>
