<HEADLINE> China to Reduce Luxury Real Estate Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- A recent issue of "China
Information" reported that China plans to tighten the reins on
luxury real estate development projects.
</P>
<P>
China will adhere to a policy of developing ordinary
apartments, rather than the development of luxury apartments
characteristics of the past few years, according to an official
with the Ministry of Construction.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey indicated that investments in luxury apartment
complexes accounted for a major share of the real estate sector
over the past few years years, with related transactions holding
respective 32.8 percent and 44.3 percent shares of the total
market volume in 1995 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
The proportional investment in the construction of ordinary
housing residences declined from 82.7 percent in 1994 to 55.7
percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The tightening on luxury real estate development will remain in
place for the foreseeable future in order to transform the current
investment structure, according to the official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
