<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Following a 13-day violence
sparked off by a border dispute, residents in the border area
between Migori and Guchad districts in southwest Kenya have
started returning to their homes, the Daily Nation reported
today.
</P>
<P>
A police source was quoted as saying that no ugly incidents
had been reported in the past two days and calm had returned to
the clash-hit area.
</P>
<P>
