both General Service Unit personnel and police officers were
still patrolling the area until the situation returns to normal.
</P>
<P>
Eight people were killed, scores injured and a lot of property
destroyed in a series of clashes between the local Luo and Kisii
tribes over border disputes in the past 13 days,.
</P>
<P>
Nyanza Provincial Commissioner Wilson Chepkwony said last week
that the Kenyan government was investigating the political motive
in the tribal clashes.
</P>
<P>
The government will take stern measures against instigators of
violence along the common borders. Meanwhile chiefs and clan
elders were urged to hold consultation meetings to iron out their
differes, a district commissioner was quoted as saying.
</P>
