<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> s d s  2547 China-Three Gorges-Competition Mechanism Market Mechanism Boosts Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- The
introduction of a market mechanism has given the Three Gorges
Project (TGP), now in full swing, a strong boost over the past
five years.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the accelerated construction process and
satisfactory quality in line with designed requirements, the
project developer China Yangtze Three Gorges Project Development
Corporation (CYTGPDC) has managed to cut down on the scale of
investment effectively, according to a company official.
</P>
<P>
Labeled as the world's largest water control project under
construction, the TGP is expected to cost 25 billion US dollars
and take 17 years to complete, the official said. Therefore, he
added, the management system that has been adopted is of crucial
importance to the quality and efficiency of the project.
</P>
<P>
The CYTGPDC, designated by the State Council as the project
developer of the Three Gorges Project, is expected to take full
responsibility of the whole project, according to the official.
</P>
<P>
"From the very start, we introduced the market mechanism and
gave high priority to efficiency," according to the official.
</P>
<P>
The market mechanism in turn resulted in mounting competition,
and the project's great amount of construction work and huge
demand for materials and equipment drew both domestic and overseas
businesses.
</P>
<P>
And competition prompted the project to gather the best
construction forces in China and pool the world's most advanced
construction machinery, thus laying a sound basis for guaranteeing
the project's quality and construction period.
</P>
<P>
Although the construction of the project was open only to
domestic engineering firms, companies from overseas competed each
other in international biddings for supply of large-scale
construction machinery and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Almost all the prestigious generator manufacturers in the world
turned up to bid for the project's most lucrative contract, the
official said, and two European consortia were finally awarded the
opportunity to supply 740 million US dollars' worth of generators
and turbines.
</P>
<P>
The blocking of the Yangtze this November 8 signals the start
of the second-phase construction work of the Three Gorges Project.
"With a market mechanism maturing after five years of practice,
people can be assured that quality and efficiency of the Three
Gorges Project will have a reliable guarantee in the remaining
construction period of 12 years," said the official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
