<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Acupuncture Being Used To Reduce Facial Wrinkles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Those who want to have smoother
skin and a younger look may have found an ally in acupuncture,
people attending a world conference in Beijing on acupuncture and
moxibustion were told today.
</P>
<P>
Needles stimulating the meridians and acupoints can improve
people's looks by balancing the function of inner organs and
promoting blood circulation and metabolism, an Indonesian
acupuncture expert, who taking part in the Academic Conference of
the World federation of Acupuncture-Moxibustion Society (WTAS),
announced.
</P>
<P>
Juliana Tjandra, vice-chairman of the Indonesian National
Acupuncture and Moxibustion Association, reports that massaging or
stimulating acupoints in the face with needles or laser beams can
smooth out wrinkle at the corners of the eyes and on the forehead.
</P>
<P>
She said that, according to clinical studies, the therapy has
proved effective on about 92 percent of 192 people, aged 30 to 78,
of whom three-forths are women.
</P>
<P>
In addition to aging, the environment, morale, ailments,
hormones, lack of sleep, and smoking can also affect the balance
of inner organs and cause wrinkles on the face or other skin
problems, she pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Because acupuncture balances the inner parts of the human body,
other methods of improving looks are often only skin-deep,
Ms. Tjandra said.
</P>
<P>
"It is also comparatively cheap," she said, explaining that in
Indonesia, a face-lift operation costs 3,000 US dollars, while
acupuncture therapy for the face costs about a tenth of that.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jointly Financed Power Plant in Shanghai Suburbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 3 (Xinhua) --The Songjiang Industrial Zone
in Shanghai and the US-based Entergy Power Co. Ltd. have announced
the decision of establishing a joint venture.
</P>
<P>
The new joint venture, the Songjiang Entergy Heat and Power
Co., will construct a heat and power plant at a cost of 29.95
million US dollars. The plant will provide central heating for the
Songjiang Industrial Zone and neighboring areas.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project will begin this year and will be
completed in 1998. The plant, which will feature two
turbogenerators with a combined generating capacity of 12
megawatts and supply 150 cu.m. of heat per hour, is designed to
keep discharges of carbon dioxide, smoke and dust particles to a
minimum.
</P>
<P>
The Songjiang Industrial Zone, located 30 km. from downtown
Shanghai, will cover 20.56 sq,km., with nine sq.km. developed
since 1992.
</P>
<P>
The zone is currently home to over 230 enterprises involving
total investments of 1.4 billion U.S. dollars. Some 170 of 230
enterprises involve foreign funding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
