<HEADLINE> China Profitable for Overseas Banks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Overseas banks in China have a
good profit record in general, and the majority begin to show a
profit after two years, the overseas edition of People's Daily
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Xunhai, deputy director of the department overseeing
overseas financial institutions in China's central bank, said that
overseas financial institutions had destablished 540
representative offices and 162 banks and other agencies in China
by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
These include 134 branches of foreign banks, seven
joint-venture banks, five solely foreign-funded banks, six
overseas financial companies, eight branch insurance companies,
one Sino-overseas joint-venture insurance firm and one
Sino-overseas investment bank.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, overseas banks in China had 32.96 billion
US dollars in total assets, 23.08 billion US dollars in
outstanding loans, and 3.99 billion US dollars in deposits.
</P>
<P>
Overseas financial institutions have been allowed to establish
agencies in 23 cities. Nine overseas banks in Shanghai's Pudong
New Area can deal in the Chinese currency, the Renminbi.
</P>
<P>
"Overseas financial institutions have helped to boost financial
competition, raise the level of financial modernization, and
introduce into China advanced techniques, financial tools and
management expertise," Zhang said. By the end of June, 89 percent
of loans issued by the overseas banks in China were for people
inside the country and nearly half were for medium- and long-term
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
