<HEADLINE> Guizhou Seeks Road to Wealth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Bijie, a poverty-stricken
mountain area in southwest China's Guizhou Province, will extend
great effort to develop animal husbandry, as well as the local
tobacco industry and township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Bijie, located in northwest Guizhou Province, features a karst
topography and severe traffic congestion. The area plans to
alleviate poverty by readjusting the rural industrial structure
and ensuring the rational use of resources.
</P>
<P>
The area will fully consider natural conditions and place
greater emphasis on raising cattle and sheep.
</P>
<P>
The plans for the development of animal husbandry in Bijie call
for the area's annual output from animal husbandry to hit 1.25
billion yuan (15.6 million U.S. dollars) by the year 2000, with
the figure to rise to two billion yuan by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Animal husbandry will become the pillar industry in Bijie and
will be a major factor enabling the area to escape poverty.
</P>
</TEXT>
