<HEADLINE> North China's Province Fulfills Plan for Autumn Wheat Planting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Hebei province, a major
north China winter wheat producer, has completed planting on 2.7
million ha of land, 133,300 ha more than in the past.
</P>
<P>
Autumn planting began on September 20, three to five days
earlier than in previous years.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has experienced its most severe drought since the
founding of new China in 1949, this year. The hot and dry weather
of the past five months hampered farming efforts this fall.
</P>
<P>
