<HEADLINE> Tianjin Benefits from Foreign Government Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Government loans from 14
countries and regions have contributed greatly to Tianjin's
economic growth, according to a municipal official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 1.32 billion U.S. dollars in foreign
government loans, or half of the north China port city's total
overseas funding, have been committed to infrastructure
construction and development of the machine-building, petroleum,
posts and telecommunications and electronics sectors.
