<HEADLINE> Tropical Storm Linda Hits Southern Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- At least three people died and 12
others went missing when tropical rainstorms hit southern Vietnam
Sunday night, media reports said today.
</P>
<P>
Typhoon Linda, with winds of about 102 kilometers per hour, hit
Ho Chi Minh City and Mekong Delta on Sundy. It was moving quickly
from west to north-west after hitting southern Vietnam to a width
of about 500 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
At least 100 fishing trawlers were capsized off Con Dao island,
the country's southern tip, and 20 trawlers may have been sunk.
</P>
<P>
Linda, the fifth storm to hit Vietnam so far this season, is
expected to generate huge waves in both the South China Sea and
the Gulf of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The storm, feared to be the worst to hit the region in 100
years, may have caused serious damages to 13 provinces in Mekong
Delta. 
</P>
