<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> From First Dam on Yangtze to Biggest Hydro-Project in the World (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANDOUPING (Three Gorges), November 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese
engineers and workers have embarked on a journey to scale the
world's summit in water control and power generation by building
the Three Gorges project with the world's largest hydro-power
station, after the Gezhouba project was completed nine years ago.
</P>
<P>
A hydroelectric power station with a total installed capacity
of 18.2 million kw will be erected in the Three Gorges Project,
compared with 12.6 million kw in Brazil's Itaipu project completed
six years ago, currently the world's No.1.
</P>
<P>
The gigantic project, aimed primarily at flood control at the
middle and lower reaches in China's No.1 and the world's No.3
river, was approved by the National People's Congress on April 3,
1992, - with 1,767 deputies for, 177 against, and 664 abstaining
after decades of investigation, planning and debate.
</P>
<P>
On today's Three Gorges worksite, the bulk of builders have
come from the Gezhouba Group since they are the only ones and the
most experienced in building a dam and hydroelectric facilities on
the mainstream of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Looking back to the days of building the Gezhouba, they are
convinced that China's present stability and prosperity guarantee
the smooth progress in construction of the Three Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
The first phase construction of the Three Gorges project is
soon to be completed with the scheduled river blocking on November
8 after five years of construction, whereas that of the smaller
Gezhouba project took ten years from 1971 to 1980 to complete, as
a result of the turmoil during the 1966-1976 Cultural Revolution.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> From First Dam on Yangtze to Biggest Hydro-Project in the World (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"With a democratic and scientific decision-making process,
something that has been learned from the lesson drawn from the
Gezhouba project, the Three Gorges project will be made a much
better one," said water conservation expert Wei Tingzheng.
</P>
<P>
China's growing national strength also guarantees the projected
25 billion US dollars of investment for the Three Gorges project,
as against 4.8 billion yuan for the Gezhouba project.
</P>
<P>
The total investment for the Three Gorges project, spanning
1993-2009 is estimated to account for less than one thousand of
the cumulative GDP during the period.
</P>
<P>
The fund for the project will come from the state allocations,
the bond and stock, and from overseas financial sources, said Li
Yong'an, deputy general manager in charge of finance of the China
Yangtze Three Gorges Project Development Corp., the project's
proprietor.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, science and technology have played a major role in
both projects, said Chen Xiaolin, Gezhouba Group's chief engineer
for the river damming.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the aid of the sophisticated computers and electronic
detectors, builders of the Three Gorges project gradually solving
the 20-plus most-knotty technical problems involving removal of a
huge amount of rocks, boulders and earth and the pouring of
concrete.
</P>
<P>
And construction equipment in use at the Three Gorges worksite
is more advanced than that used by the Gezhouba project, such as
the 77-ton US made Caterpillar self-tipping trucks instead of the
30-ton ones most commonly use at the Gezhouba worksite.  
</P>
</TEXT>
