<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Star Alliance to Admit Brazil's Varig </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Star Alliance, a five-member
partnership, will admit Varig, an airline from Brazil, as its
sixth member, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony for admitting the new member will be held
in Phuket in southern Thailand soon.
</P>
<P>
The multi-partner aviation transport joint venture will undergo
a reorganization before it admits Varig.
</P>
<P>
Star Alliance currently comprises United Airlines, Lufthansa,
Scandinavian Airlines (SAS), Air Canada and Thai Airways.
</P>
<P>
With Varig as its sixth member, the investment stake in the
venture from each partner will change slightly, with United
Airlines, SAS, Lufthansa each holding 22.5 percent and the rest
holding 10.83 percent each.  
</P>
</TEXT>
