<HEADLINE> Russian President Preparing China Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
is preparing a state visit to China, presidential press secretary
Sergei Yastrzhembsky said today.
</P>
<P>
The preparation work, Yastrzhembsky noted, began after
Yeltsin's informal summit with Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro
Hashimoto ended today in Siberia.
</P>
<P>
Russia hopes Yeltsin's China tour could strengthen the existing
political momentum for building a Russia-China strategic
partnership oriented towards the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
It also expects the forthcoming Russia-China summit in Beijing
to analyze in details various factors that are blocking extensive
economic cooperation between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Also today, Russia's Deputy Foreign Minister Grigori Karasin
told the Itar-Tass news agency that Russia-China relations have
entered into maturity, with bright prospects for future expansion.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is scheduled to begin his three-day China visit on
November 9, and has a plan to tour Harbin, capital of northeast
China's Heilongjiang Province bordering Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
