<HEADLINE> International Silk Congress to Be Held in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Silk
Association will hold its 21st congress in the Thai capital of
Bangkok on November 3-7, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the association was quoted as saying that
the meeting will be attended by 150 representatives from 39
countries, most of whom are entrepreneurs and executives of the
silk trade.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which aims to improve opportunities for the silk
trade, will discuss topics including silk trade promotion, trade
in raw silk and silk fabrics, sericulture and silk reeling, and
sericulture development as well as technology development.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also review silk manufactures and trade in
recent years, and changes in the industry and its future. 
</P>
