<HEADLINE> Mexico Qualifies for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Mexico qualified for the
1998 World Cup finals after drawing the United States 0-0 in a
qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The tie guaranteed Mexico a trip to the World Cup finals in
France and at the same time kept alive American team's hopes of
becoming one of the three qualifiers from the North and Central
American and Caribbean region.
</P>
<P>
The American team played most of the game with 10 men as Jeff
Agoos was sent off at the 32nd minute for elbowing Pavel Pardo.
</P>
<P>
Bora Milutinovic, head coach of the Mexican team, said he was
content that his team advanced into the World Cup finals. But he
said he was not satisfied with the result.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican team now have 16 points from four wins and four
draws, followed by Mamaica with 12 points from 3 wins, three draws
against 2 losses. The United States are third with 11 points.
</P>
