<HEADLINE> Spaniard Wins Colombia Open Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, Colombia, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Francisco
Clavet of Spain won his second straight ATP title after beating
Ecuador's Nicolas Lapentti 6-3, 6-3 at the Colombia Open final on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Clavet broke Lapentti in the opening game of the match, then
broke him again in the ninth game before winning the set in 44
minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Clavet went up 4-2 with a break in the sixth
game. He went on to complete the match by holding serve from
love-30.
</P>
<P>
Clavet has won 10 straight matches and 18 of 21 since a
first-round loss at the U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
It was Clavet's fifth title in his career. The 1995 winner
Lapentti played in his third consecutive Colombia Open final.
</P>
</TEXT>
