<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Issues 1st Local Law Protecting Private Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital city of
the reform-pioneering Guangdong Province in south China, recently
enacted a set of regulations covering the rights and interests of
private enterprises. It is the first such law published in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Under the new law, private companies are allowed to participate
in the restructuring of state-owned enterprises by contracting,
leasing, merging and purchasing state-run or collectively-owned
firms.
</P>
<P>
Private economy has been booming in the city since the country
launched the reform and opening drive in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, by the first half of this year,
the city had 22,507 private enterprises, with a staff of 219,760
and a capital of 17.04 billion yuan, and 200,660 privately-run
businesses, with a staff of 339,851 and a capital of 2.58 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, local private businessmen handed over 1.24 billion
yuan in taxes to the state coffer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971103.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Corporations Biggest Investors in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 3 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine US transnational
corporations have invested 2.34 million U.S. dollars in the Pudong
Economic Zone, accounting for 26.6 percent of the total investment
of 109 transnational corporations.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest statistics from the customs office of
Pudong, with the large-scale investment volume, 73 percent of the
total of all American enterprises in Pudong, the 29 corporations
have plunged into many high-tech sectors.
</P>
<P>
Large corporations such as Hughes Aircraft, General Motors,
Kodak and Motorola have invested in satellite communications,
automobiles, precision instrument manufacturing, energy and
electronic appliances.
</P>
<P>
The biggest joint-venture program in Pudong, and the biggest
American project in China, is General Motors' investment of 1.52
billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
