<HEADLINE> Sampras Captures Seventh Title in Paris Indoor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras of the United States
cracked 12th-seeded Jonas Bjorkman of Sweden 6-3, 4-6, 6-3, 6-1 in
the final of the Paris Indoor Open on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old American needed two hours and 11 minutes to
capture his seventh title of the season, though he went to a
clinic late Saturday to test for a painful right shoulder and
upper arm and he needed painkillers before Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who has currently won 51 tournaments and 10 Grand Slam
singles titles since 1988, finished the year on top of the
rankings for a fifth consecutive time.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman, 25, who started the season a 69th in the rankings and
entered the world's top 10 for the first time last Monday when he
took 10th spot after reaching the semi-finals in Stuttgart, will
reach to a career-best fourth in the rankings on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
