<HEADLINE> Chinese President Visits Hughes Electronics Corporation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles, November 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin, who arrived here Saturday afternoon on the last leg of his
U.S. tour, visited Hughes Electronics Corporation this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, an electronics expert himself, showed great interest
during the entire two-hour tour and asked many detailed and
specific questions.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the Hughes Corporate headquarters by Michael
T Smith, new chairman and chief executive officer of Hughes
Electronics, and John F Smith Jr, chairman and chief executive
officer and president of General Motors Corporation.
</P>
<P>
After brief welcome remarks made by the two CEOs, President
Jiang toured displays of the latest in Hughes high technology
electronics, including DIRECTV, DirccPC and live Beijing
television via the PanAMSAT global satellite network.
</P>
<P>
Of th offerings of GM technologies Jiang was shown were the
vehicles featuring the latest concept in safety, security and
communications, the Buick Regal which will be produced in China
starting in 1999, and a proposed multi-purpose people's car for
China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and his entourage then toured the Hughes Integrated
Satellite Factory in nearby EL Segundo. The Hughes Space and
Communications facility is the world's largest manufacturer of
commercial communications satellites.
</P>
<P>
Before a luncheon with local dignitaries, President Jiang met
with governor of California Pete Wilson and mayor of Los Angeles
Richard Riordan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
